<p dir=3D"auto">The following pins have glitches during power up.</p>
<p dir=3D"auto">GPIO1, GPIO2,GPIO3,GPIO4, GPIO5, GPIO6, GPIO7, GPIO8, GPIO9=
, GPIO10, GPIO11, GPIO12, GPIO13, GPIO14, GPIO15, GPIO16, GPIO17:</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto">
<li>Low-level glitch: the pin is at a low level output status for 60us.</li=
>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto">GPIO18:</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto">
<li>Low-level glitch: the pin is at a low level output status for 60us.</li=
>
<li>High-level glitch: the pin is at a high level output status for 60us.</=
li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto">GPIO19, GPIO20:</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto">
<li>Low-level glitch: the pin is at a low level output status for 60us.</li=
>
<li>Two High-level glitches: the pin is at a high level output status for 6=
0us.</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto">See Table-2-2 <a href=3D"https://www.espressif.com/sites/de=
fault/files/documentation/esp32-s3_datasheet_en.pdf" rel=3D"nofollow">here<=
/a></p>
