<p dir=3D"auto">there are cases where the Pin is by Default connected to a =
+3.3V or a +1.8V Power Domain.
Examples are GPIO20 (D+) or GPIO48.</p>
<p dir=3D"auto">you can switch them off in a very early stage in Bootloader=
:</p>
<p dir=3D"auto"><a href=3D"https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf/tree/master=
/examples/custom_bootloader/bootloader_hooks">see here</a></p>
<p dir=3D"auto">with e.g. the Following Code:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight highlight-source-c notranslate position-relative ov=
erflow-auto" dir=3D"auto"><pre><span class=3D"pl-smi">void</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"pl-en">bootloader_before_init</span>(<span class=3D"pl-smi">void</spa=
n>) {
    <span class=3D"pl-c">/* Keep in my mind that a lot of functions cannot =
be called from here</span>
<span class=3D"pl-c">     * as system initialization has not been performed=
 yet, including</span>
<span class=3D"pl-c">     * BSS, SPI flash, or memory protection. */</span>
    <span class=3D"pl-en">ESP_LOGI</span>(<span class=3D"pl-s">"HOOK"</span=
>, <span class=3D"pl-s">"This hook is called BEFORE bootloader initializati=
on"</span>);
    <span class=3D"pl-en">gpio_hal_iomux_func_sel</span>(<span class=3D"pl-=
c1">GPIO_PIN_MUX_REG</span>[<span class=3D"pl-c1">GPIO_NUM_20</span>], <spa=
n class=3D"pl-c1">PIN_FUNC_GPIO</span>);
    <span class=3D"pl-en">esp_rom_gpio_pad_select_gpio</span>(<span class=
=3D"pl-c1">GPIO_NUM_48</span>);
    <span class=3D"pl-en">gpio_ll_output_enable</span> (<span class=3D"pl-c=
1">&amp;</span><span class=3D"pl-c1">GPIO</span>, <span class=3D"pl-c1">GPI=
O_NUM_48</span>);
    <span class=3D"pl-en">gpio_ll_set_level</span> (<span class=3D"pl-c1">&=
amp;</span><span class=3D"pl-c1">GPIO</span>, <span class=3D"pl-c1">GPIO_NU=
M_48</span>, <span class=3D"pl-c1">0</span>);
}</pre><div class=3D"zeroclipboard-container">
    <clipboard-copy aria-label=3D"Copy" class=3D"ClipboardButton btn btn-in=
visible js-clipboard-copy m-2 p-0 d-flex flex-justify-center flex-items-cen=
ter" data-copy-feedback=3D"Copied!" data-tooltip-direction=3D"w" value=3D"v=
oid bootloader_before_init(void) {
    /* Keep in my mind that a lot of functions cannot be called from here
     * as system initialization has not been performed yet, including
     * BSS, SPI flash, or memory protection. */
    ESP_LOGI(&quot;HOOK&quot;, &quot;This hook is called BEFORE bootloader =
initialization&quot;);
    gpio_hal_iomux_func_sel(GPIO_PIN_MUX_REG[GPIO_NUM_20], PIN_FUNC_GPIO);
    esp_rom_gpio_pad_select_gpio(GPIO_NUM_48);
    gpio_ll_output_enable (&amp;GPIO, GPIO_NUM_48);
    gpio_ll_set_level (&amp;GPIO, GPIO_NUM_48, 0);
}" tabindex=3D"0" role=3D"button">
